text: अलीपुरद्वार में @AmitShah ने 11 गोरखा जनजातियों को आदिवासी का दर्जा देने का वादा किया. चाय बागान मजदूरों की मजदूरी बढ़ाने का आश्वासन दिया. बीजेपी की बंगाल फतह योजना 2019 में उत्तर बंगाल में हासिल बढ़त पर टिकी है. शाह बार-बार दोहरा रहे हैं कि कैसे दीदी ने उत्तर को नजरअंदाज किया. https://t.co/j3jmlAcQZV

text: Those injected with the vaccine should start developing anti-bodies in 15 days time. Oxford University vaccine has a 70%+ efficacy after one month according to scientists and if second dose is taken after three months efficacy increases to 90%+.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Prof Adrian Hil feels rather than getting caught in a 70 vs 80 vs 90% vaccine efficacy debate, it is more important to ensure global rollout at scale and low cost. All approved vaccines are proven to show that people don’t get a terrible bout of the Covid infection.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Dr Adrian Hill who helped develop Oxford University vaccine tells @IndiaToday the vaccine has an 80% efficacy if administered at a gap of three months between the two doses and is more efficacious with a longer gap than with the 28 day gap originally which was originally proposed

name: Rahul Kanwal
text:
Professor Adrian Hill
Vaccinologist & Director, Jenner Institute
Prof. of Human Genetics at Oxford University joins me live on @IndiaToday at 8 pm #Newstrack Key scientist who helped develop the vaccine which got approval this morning.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Join me on @IndiaToday this Sunday 8-10 pm as we try to answer all the questions swirling in your mind about the vaccine approvals. DG ICMR Dr Balram Bharghav, Dr Adrian Hill, Director of Jenner Institute, Oxford University, @adarpoonawalla CEO Serum, Dr VK Paul of Niti Aayog.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: The Drug Controller of India did not take questions in this morning’s briefing. But the DG of ICMR Dr Balram Bharghav has answered many critical questions and shared insights into thinking in Govt on the two vaccines that got approval in this @IndiaToday interview. Worth a watch. https://t.co/unTS5QvC5d

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: ICMR believes Bharat Biotech’s Covaxin may be able to better cope with UK mutation than the Astra Zeneca vaccine since Covaxin is a whole virus vaccine. Which is why emergency use approval has been granted according to Dr Bharghav. Phase 3 trial results should be out in 3-4 weeks

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Dr Balram Bharghav, DG, ICMR tells @IndiaToday Emergency use authorisation means only Govt can procure and distribute the two vaccines. Vaccines can be sold in private sector only after full licensure is granted. Data will be reviewed every week by regulatory authorities.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: There are a thousand questions people have about vaccines. Not okay for Drug Controller not to take questions. DCGI needs to assure citizens about the thoroughness of the process that has been undertaken by the authorities. Vaccine efficacy trial results should be made public.

text: Unlike the Kangaroo Court he runs, I believe Arnab Goswami deserves a fair trial and the Mumbai Police needs to prove these charges in a court of law not in a press conference. The weight of evidence is what matters most. Your view or bias doesn’t matter. What matters is proof.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: TRP ratings were being bought. Viewership data was being manipulated reveals Mumbai Police Commissioner Singh. BARC filed a complaint with the Mumbai police. Commissioner hopes to take probe to conclusion very soon. Satyamev Jayate. Ultimately the truth has a way of coming out.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Mumbai Police Commissioner suspects current employees of Hansa research could also be involved in the scam. Ex employees of Hansa have been arrested. Arnab Goswami to be called in for questioning for fixing ratings. Summons being issued shortly.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Owners and directors of @republic TV will be called in for questioning to answer Mumbai Police questions on why they were fixing news viewership. Advertisers will be asked whether they were victims of the crime or party to the racket says Mumbai Police Commissioner Singh.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: What's long been suspected by industry insiders now exposed as part of an elaborate investigation by Mumbai Police. Commissioner reveals @republic TV was paying households with @BARCIndia meters to keep Republic channels turned on at home. And remember this expose is in one city.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Mumbai Commissioner alleges @republic TV owner involved in a scam to fix ratings. Singh says charge of criminal breach of trust and cheating filed against owners of 3 channels that were fixing data. Two channel owners arrested. @republic owner/directors to be questioned soon.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Mumbai Commissioner says some ex-employees of Hansa research were in cahoots with some news channels. Hansa revealed to news channels details of where @BARCIndia meters were installed. Poor uneducated people paid money every month to keep English news channels on their screen!

name: Rahul Kanwal

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: First they levelled all manner of charges on @Tweet2Rhea In their Kangaroo Court, Rhea was declared guilty and sentenced. Now when a REAL JUDGE has given bail & refuted the most serious charges, they won’t even mention that Rhea got bail. This is what happens in a Banana Republic

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Bombay High Court Judge: Allegations against @Tweet2Rhea of spending money in procuring drugs for @itsSSR does not mean she financed illicit drug traffic." "SSR had no criminal case or FIR pending. No apprehension of arrest. Therefore, Rhea cannot be said to be harbouring SSR."

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Everyone who was baying for @Tweet2Rhea blood should read Bombay High Court order. These are findings of a real JUDGE. Not some monkey who thinks he is judge, jury and execution. Judge has examined all evidence placed by NCB to conclude Rhea was not a part of drug dealers.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Bombay HC bail order in @Tweet2Rhea case is a blow to charges filed by NCB. Judge finds no evidence to suggest Rhea financed drug trade, which was key to the stringent charge of Sec 27A under NDPS Act. 'Helping procure drugs for Sushant not same as harbouring and financing drugs'

text: There are rare times when a team rolls out a project that is truly pathbreaking. Today’s aerial simulation of confrontation along LAC is a novel experiment in story telling. name: Rahul Kanwal
text: When you do something innovative you wonder how it will be received in the end. Will viewers be dazzled by what they see or will the entire effort bomb. There’s no real way of knowing. But at least we tried to do something new. Would love your feedback. Good, bad, ugly. Do watch.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: In order to make a political point, some pundits mixed up three different metrics. Compared apples with oranges. If you compare apples with apples and oranges with oranges the story is still the same. India’s economy has been most badly hit. Don’t shoot the data or the messenger. https://t.co/bCZmv3BiXA

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: When the thought crossed my mind, I had no clear idea of how much time/effort it would take. The new project has taken 5X amount of estimated effort. But what’s really amazing about @IndiaToday & @aajtak is everyone’s really excited about making what seemed impossible come alive.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Our labour continues. Big things take longer than expected to bring together. Watch this space. Tomorrow.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Been working on a special project for the last three days. Do tune into our coverage across platforms of the @IndiaToday & @aajtak this evening. It’s been a Herculean effort to try and bring this idea together. Your feedback would be most welcome.

name: Rahul Kanwal
Rahul Kanwal
text: Questions were asked about this @BT_India chart. Numbers were checked again. Alas, India’s economy has been mostly badly ravaged by the pandemic among major global economies. Economists and sundry pundits who had raised questions have accepted their error. Updated numbers below. https://t.co/lR9R2JRAbg

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Data released by International Monetary Fund @IMFNews Chief Economist @GitaGopinath shows Indian economy having fared the worst among big economies of the world in Apr-Jun quarter 2020. Instead of attacking the data, let’s attack the recession and work hard towards bouncing back. https://t.co/632kfD4HGL

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: He worked with us for only two years, but even in this short stint @neelanshu512 made a lifetime of friends and earned a legion of admirers. Colleagues of our dear departed reporter shared their tributes and memories during an online remembrance meet. We miss you Neelanshu. https://t.co/93SCvpk7Hr

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Indian External Affairs ministry alleges China tried to carry out aggressive military manoeuvres yesterday as well even as Brigadier level talks were going on. Situation along LAC is like a tinderbox waiting to explode. Latest inside story coming up on #Newstrack at 8 PM. https://t.co/zTkD6QPxCf

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Details emerge of the action mounted by Indian army special forces against PLA in South Bank of Panggong Tso. Belligerent China threatens retaliation and pull back. Are we now in a quid pro quo situation? Will crisis dial down from here? Or escalate further? #Newstrack 8 PM.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Home Minister @AmitShah back in action after recovering from Covid. Wishing him good health. https://t.co/CkVXVwV5k7

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: @nagarjund @IndiaToday Welcome back Naga. You were missed. It's good to have you back in action. Glad to know you have recovered.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Any wisecrack who thinks let’s just get the virus and get on with life needs a reality check. The Covid-19 virus reacts in unpredictable ways in a human body. Age is no defence. Our young colleague had no known medical conditions and yet succumbed to the virus. Pl be v cautious.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Shattered with the demise of our dear colleague and India Today’s Lucknow correspondent @neelanshu512 A terrible bout of Covid claimed the life of this intrepid 30 year old reporter. The entire team is plagued with grief. May God give strength to his family and friends. Om Shanti

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: There will be a Chinese response. Of that no one should have any doubt. When? Where? Localised or extended? No one can know for sure. When you sleep tonight, say a prayer for our brave jawans who are deployed at inhospitable heights guarding India from the dragon’s designs.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: For long a debate has raged in our country over whether we needed the Special Frontier Forces (SFF) and what role they would play when relations between India-China seemed to be getting better. Using the Vikas Regiment manned by Tibetan soldiers sends a powerful message to China.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: For too long we have taken a hit and questions have been asked about what we were going to do. The Special Frontier Forces have shown immense daring. Big salute. The Dragon needs to be confronted. Cannot allow China to bully India. 1.3 billion people will strike back. Game on.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: What’s good for the goose, is good for the gander. The goose is now going crazy. Jai Ho.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: As predicted previously, China sparks a border skirmish and then seeks to pin the blame on India. Same modus operandi has in decades gone by led to major global wars. Now threatening 'retaliation to Indian provocation.' Classic case of Ulta Chor Kotwal Ko Dante. Guns loaded... https://t.co/ZRfL3yrCyi

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Worst economic performance in 24 years! India's Q1 GDP contracts 23.9% in Apr-June quarter. This is the biggest contraction globally among the major economies of the world in the aftermath of the #Covid pandemic. https://t.co/rh3vKJjq33 https://t.co/ex4aqkaByg

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Pranab Da was an unmatched Encyclopedia of politics. Very few netas could explain policy minutiae or protocols to reporters like Dada. Remember being scolded by him a few times, about questions that I had posed. But after the outburst, he would always come around. RIP. Om Shanti.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Sushant’s family has said they didn’t know about his mental illness. But new WhatsApp chats accessed by India Today show exchanges between Sushant and his sister Priyanka where the sister is arranging depression medicines and telling SSR to have his pills. https://t.co/FvJXUjmYqY

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: From roads to stealth fighter jets to missile batteries, China is going all out to build pressure on the border with India. India Today OSINT desk brings into focus a sudden growth in Chinese air defence sites. https://t.co/g9G8TY7C2h

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: China pushing India to act against PLA aggression. If India responds militarily, China will then blame India for initiating escalation. PLA intent very clear. Nothing will come out of military-diplomatic talks. Onus on India on how to respond to Chinese military adventurism.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: https://t.co/1oCt00off9

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: In the way the confrontation is shaping up between Indian and Chinese armies, it seems we are heading towards a military conflict. And once the balloon goes up, there's no telling where things will end. PLA refusing to restore status quo and Indian Army in no mood to cow down.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Metros to re-open from Sept 7. Religious and social functions with 100 people allowed from Sept 21. Schools to remain closed till Sept 30. Swimming pools, theatres cannot open. No restriction on inter-state travel. No relaxation in containment zones. Breaking #Newstrack at 8 pm.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Problem with SSR coverage is one news channel and its copycats are making up facts as they go along. You need to stop, assess whether what is being charged is true or not and then form an opinion. Forming firm views on the basis of WhatsApp University is dangerous. #Newstrack 8pm

text: मजबूत लोकतंत्र में एक मजबूत विपक्ष की जरूरत होती है. कई मतदाता ऐसी कांग्रेस का इंतजार कर रहे हैं जो जोरदार ढंग से सरकार विरोधी एजेंडे पर आगे बढ़े. लेकिन लगता है कि जो लोग कांग्रेस में हैं, उनमें लड़ने के लिए कलेजा नहीं बचा है. सत्ता और अधिकार की भावना ने उन्हें कमजोर कर दिया है.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: गांधी परिवार के करीबी समझे जाने वाले एक सीनियर कांग्रेसी का कहना है, आप कल्पना नहीं कर सकते कि हममें से कितने लोग बीजेपी में जाने के लिए बातचीत कर रहे हैं. अब सवाल है कि क्या कुछ और नेता जहाज से कूदना पसंद करेंगे या उनमें से कुछ पार्टी में रहते हुए भीतर से सुधार का साहस करेंगे.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: A functional democracy requires a feisty opposition. Enough and more voters are yearning for a Congress that can effectively champion an anti-government agenda. But those within Congress seem to have no stomach for a fight. Power and a sense of entitlement have corroded them.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Senior Congress leader, usually considered close to the Gandhis, says you can’t imagine how many of us are in talks to switch over to the BJP. Question is will more leaders choose to jump from the ship or can some of them at least muster the courage to try and reform from within.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: कांग्रेस का नेतृत्व @RahulGandhi करें, @BJP4India के लिए इससे अच्छी स्थिति नहीं हो सकती. वोटर @narendramodi का अच्छा और बुरा ट्रैक रिकॉर्ड देखेंगे. यह भी देखेंगे कि उनके खिलाफ कौन है. परिवार के बाहर यह स्थिति ​हर किसी के लिए पूरी तरह साफ है. ज्यादातर कांग्रेसी भी यह जानते हैं.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: अब @JM_Scindia कांग्रेस से @BJP4India में चले गए हैं और @SachinPilot का पार्टी में रहना मुश्किल हो गया है. ऐसे में कांग्रेसियों के पास सीमित विकल्प हैं. अब वे @RahulGandhi से कहेंगे, आप ही नैया पार लगाइए. नेतृत्व से न हटकर गांधी परिवार पार्टी को सियासी खुदकुशी की तरफ धकेल रहा है.

text: राजमाता का बेटे के प्रति अंधा प्रेम सच देखने से इनकार कर रहा है और @INCIndia को सियासी प्रलय की ओर धकेल रहा है. @RahulGandhi अपनी अयोग्यता साबित करने का एक भी मौका नहीं चूकते. राहुल गांधी राजनीति के लिए नहीं बने हैं. सोनिया गांधी और खुद राहुल के अलावा पूरा भारत ये बात समझता है.

text: आज की @INCIndia में दो युवा नेता ऐसे थे, जिनकी हिंदी पट्टी में पहचान थी और जिनमें अखिल भारतीय नेता के रूप में उभरने की क्षमता थी- एक @JM_Scindia और दूसरे @SachinPilot. सोचिए, सिंधिया के कांग्रेस छोड़ने और सचिन पायलट के ​विद्रोह करने का फायदा किसे मिलेगा. जवाब है @RahulGandhi.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: A matriarch’s blind love for her son and refusal to see reality is driving @INCIndia to political doom. @RahulGandhi has not missed a single opportunity to prove his incompetence. The man is not cut out for politics. All of India can see this, except Mrs Gandhi and RG himself.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Sachin Pilot wants @ashokgehlot51 gone at all cost. He’s reached Fidayeen zone. @ashokgehlot51 too wants @SachinPilot off his back. @INCIndia is backing Gehlot. It’s a telling indictment of Sonia Gandhi’s current state of leadership that she’s unable to resolve factional fuels.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: For @BJP4India, @RahulGandhi coming back to helm @INCIndia is a best case scenario. Voters will look at @narendramodi track record, both good and bad, look at who’s against him & pick @PMOIndia This is clear as daylight to everyone outside the Parivar, including most in Congress.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: With @JM_Scindia now in @BJP4India & @SachinPilot position in @INCIndia increasingly becoming untenable, the rump of the Congress will have little option but to back @RahulGandhi to lead them. By refusing to step aside the Gandhis are leading Congress over the abyss of relevance.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: In @INCIndia there were two young leaders -- @JM_Scindia & @SachinPilot -- who had resonance in Hindi heartland and potential to emerge as pan-India leaders. Ponder over who would be biggest beneficiary of @JM_Scindia exit & @SachinPilot rebellion. Ans: @RahulGandhi

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Minutes before #VikasDubey encounter, gangster was filmed at a toll plaza travelling in a Tata Safari. Vehicle that turned turtle in which Dubey was supposedly travelling was a Mahindra TUV 300. The cops didn’t even bother to try hard to cover their tracks. Height of brazenness.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: @shahtwitting @ReporterRavish @arvindojha Do watch our coverage on Aajtak and India Today in the evening and let us know what you think

text: #विकासदुबे को उज्जैन से कानपुर लाने के दौरान हमारे संवाददाता काफिले के साथ-साथ चल रहे थे. रात 10.30 बजे राजगढ़ में यूपी एसटीएफ ने @ReporterRavish की कार रोकी और उनकी चाबी निकाल ली. ‘एनकाउंटर’ के ठीक 15 मिनट पहले काफिले के पीछे चल रही @arvindojha की कार रोक दी गई. उसके बाद Boom.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Our correspondents were tracking #VikasDubey cavalcade non-stop from Ujjain to Kanpur. At 10:30pm @ReporterRavish car was stopped by UP STF in Rajgarh. Cops drove away with car key. Then 15 minutes before ‘encounter’ @arvindojha car was stopped from tailing convoy in Kanpur. Boom

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: This is the greatest challenge of @narendramodi political career. He didn’t choose confrontation, his supposed ‘friend’ Xi betrayed him. How India responds to China’s dare will define @PMOIndia legacy and determine India’s place in the world in the years to come.

name: Rahul Kanwal

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: When I said to Yun Sun this isn’t India of 1962, she replied this isn’t China of 1962 either. China has developed capacities since. True. But Pandit Nehru didn’t use every weapon India had. @narendramodi today has signalled India will engage every tool to defend it’s sovereignty.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: After this rousing speech to India’s military either China will find a way of disengaging or we are heading towards an escalation. PM Modi has signalled clearly India won’t be cowed down. And that the Indian Army is ready to do what it takes to defend the country. Onus on China.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: In terms of domestic and international messaging @PMOIndia has gone way beyond anyone would have anticipated. Ladakh is India’s forehead and pride. Won’t allow the head to be bowed. One country is adamant on expansionism. This country’s designs will not be allowed to succeed.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Era of expansionism is over. This is the era of development. He may not have named China directly, but @narendramodi has made clear than any nation that pushes ahead with expansionism ends up hurting world peace and ends up either defeated or having to change course.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Wow. Not in living memory has any Indian PM spoken so passionately to our soldiers at a time of a grave military crisis. Civilians can’t even begin to fathom the electrifying effect this speech is going have through the ranks of the armed forces. Terrific motivation. Shabash.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Focus initially was on Fingers area of Panggong Tso lake, then on Galwan Valley which was the site of the bloody clash between Indian and Chinese Armies. Tonight, using Open Source Satellite images we will show you the eye popping build up in the Hot Springs Sector. #Newstrack

name: Rahul Kanwal

name: Rahul Kanwal

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: After the eye-opening satellite analysed put out by @indiatoday OSINT desk, we are back with an encore. At 8 PM on #Newstrack we will expose the massive build-up by Chinese Army in the Galwan Sector. We have accessed series of new satellite images going back to 2010. Do tune in.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: High level Govt sources say Chinese army had agreed to disengage on June 6 but instead of pulling back local Chinese military commander crossed LAC. Indian Commanding Officer went to ask China to follow disengagement plan. That's when situation spiralled and violence ensued...

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: 17 Indian troops who were critically injured in the line of duty at the stand off location and exposed to sub-zero temperatures in the high altitude terrain have succumbed to their injuries, taking the total that were killed in action to 20.

text: *Official Statement * Indian and Chinese troops have disengaged at the Galwan area where they had earlier clashed on the night of 15/16 June 2020. 17 Indian troops who were critically injured in the line of duty at the stand off location have succumbed to their injuries.

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: The depth of the map making you will see on India Today hasn’t been done on Indian news TV before this. But the current stand-off, as we know, is the biggest military build up since 1962 so it’s important to dive deep to make sense of the story. #Newstrack 8 pm @IndiaToday

name: Rahul Kanwal
text: Opportunity to immerse oneself in new fields of study has to be among best things about being a journalist. One is always picking up new skills. Dad was an accomplished cartographer, grew up seeing him work on his maps. Ended up having to do the same but without his guidance :(

name: Rahul Kanwal

text: A simple statistical intuition for India’s netas: More widely you test, less Covid’s Total Positivity Ratio (TPR) is likely to be.
